any American women even as it opened opportunities for many American men. A treasure-trove of original research, the book should stimulate scholarly discussion and captivate any reader interested in the thoughts and lives of American women.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Mai 2020) 0aFeminismxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aFeminismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSex differences in educationxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aSex differences in educationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen college studentsxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomen college studentszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomenxEducation (Higher)xHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aWomenxEducation (Higher)zUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311068861008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066331040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813553191423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813553191.jpg  a978-3-11-066331-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-068861-0  RUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK